features: Built-in emulator for NES format games: The Babibubary Retro Game Stick with 1550+ Classic Video Games for TV is a mini game stick that allows you to connect it to a TV with an HDMI interface and play classic games from the 80s. It features a built-in emulator for NES format games, giving you access to a wide range of nostalgia-inducing games.
Save games: This retro game console supports saving game progress. It also supports adding new games, you can download your favorite games in NES format from the internet and add them to its system.

Wireless controllers: This extreme mini game box is equipped with 2 wireless controllers. Without the limitation of wires, the game is more free and unrestrained. You can share the fun of gaming with your family and friends.
Compatibility: This NES game stick is connected with HDMI port, it needs to be compatible with TVs with HDMI port. It also works with computer monitors and projectors with HDMI ports.

Great gift: This retro game stick is compact, easy to store and carry, it supports classic mini games from the 80s, allowing you to relive your favorite games from your childhood. It is perfect as a Thanksgiving/Christmas/New Year holiday gift for Kids and Adults.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: EASY SETUP 1. Connect the GameStick to the power supply of the USB port through the power cable, such as the USB port of the TV, the adapter in the package.2. Plug the game stick into the HDMI port of the TV.3. Tune the TV to HD channel.Tip: When there is a frozen game screen, please use the adapter in the package.
6 CATEGORIES, A TOTAL OF 1500+ CLASSIC GAMES ACTION GAME（201）PUZZLE GAME（292）RACING GAME（45）SHOOT GAME(153)SPORT GAME（96）USER FLODER（764）

HOW TO START/EXIT THE GAME 1. Please use controller 1P to select, start and exit the game.2. Please press and hold the start and select buttons at the same time, and select the option you want in the menu (exit/save/load, etc.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Games suck, not nostalgic
reviews.reviewText: I bought one of these from a website based in Florida a couple years back, amazing quality. My kids broke the controllers, I saw this listed on Amazon and decided to give it a try.-the remotes lag, big time-the games that are on the SD card are absolute trash and not nostalgic to any OG Nintendo games-im a huge Nintendo fan, and I had never even heard of these poor quality games-when plugged in behind a TV in an HDMI (like most things), the transmitter lags severely during game play.Only good thing is, the controllers worked with the old stick I already had bought from the Florida website a couple years prior. Kept the controllers, threw this game stick directly in the trash.Don't waste your money, this is a crap product

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Tons of 8bit games
reviews.reviewText: Plug and play install. It powered on instantly to the main game menu. Games are sorted by category like sports, adventure racing etc making it easy to find what your looking for. I found all my favorite classic 8-bit games. There is a lot of artifacts and pop up screen distortions. They only last a few seconds but they are constantly showing up in some games. Not sure if its the emulator or the under powered game stick. The controllers are good and you do get two for co-op play. Very fun with lots of nostalgia and glitches.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars HDMI stopped recognizing plug in
reviews.reviewText: Loved this when we got it. Plug and play was seamless. Then after about a week, the hdmi port would no longer recognize device. Tested other hdmi port on tv. Tested power cord. Nothing will resolve it. I even tried simply unplugging tv. No go. I will have to return this even though I really loved the games. I'm pretty sad about it.
